{"chapter_summary": "The chapter introduces the Vaisheshika system, defining dharma as that which leads to worldly prosperity and ultimate liberation. It enumerates the six categories (padarthas): substance, quality, action, generality, particularity, and inherence. It discusses their definitions, relations, and the nature of existence (satta).", "entities": [{"name": "dharma", "kind": "concept", "aliases": [], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.1", "KVs_1,1.2"]}, {"name": "dravya", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["substance"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5", "KVs_1,1.15"]}, {"name": "guna", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["quality"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.6", "KVs_1,1.16"]}, {"name": "karma", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["action"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.7", "KVs_1,1.17"]}, {"name": "samanya", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["generality"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,2.4", "KVs_1,2.5"]}, {"name": "visesa", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["particularity"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,2.6"]}, {"name": "samavaya", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["inherence"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.4"]}, {"name": "satta", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["existence"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,2.7", "KVs_1,2.8"]}, {"name": "pṛthivī", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["earth"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "āpaḥ", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["water"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "tejas", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["fire"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "vāyu", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["air"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "ākāśa", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["ether"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "kāla", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["time"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "dik", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["space"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "ātman", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["self"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1,1.5"]}, {"name": "manas", "kind": "concept", "aliases": ["mind"], "verse_ranges": ["KVs_1